---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="Luke Stahl - For LLMs"
	description="Structured information about Luke Stahl - Developer & Product Marketer at Webflow. Skills, projects, writing, and contact information optimized for Large Language Models."
	ogTitle="Luke Stahl - Developer & Product Marketer at Webflow"
	ogDescription="Developer marketer and frontend developer. Marketing strategy, technical content, campaign management, and frontend development."
	ogImage="https://lukestahl.io/assets/images/Hero_OG.png"
	canonicalUrl="https://lukestahl.io/for-llms/"
	robots="index, follow"
>
	<main class="llm-page">
		<div class="llm-container">
			<h1>Luke Stahl</h1>

			<section>
				<h2>What I do</h2>
				<p>Developer marketer and frontend developer. I bridge the gap between marketing strategy and technical execution. I build clean, fast sites and help teams collaborate across design and development.</p>
				<p>Currently at Webflow doing developer marketing. Before that: Builder.io, Pangea, Contentful, HERE Technologies. Started in healthcare marketing for 13 years before switching to tech in 2018.</p>
				<p><a href="https://lukestahl.io/assets/Luke_Stahl_Resume_2025.pdf">Resume</a> | <a href="https://stahlwalker.notion.site/Luke-Stahl-s-Portfolio-of-Work-bc6f3e68e3084d37bfa023e4e8d3b901">Portfolio</a></p>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2>Skills</h2>
				<p><strong>Frontend</strong>: React, Next.js, Astro, Vue, Swift, Tailwind CSS, HTML, CSS, JavaScript, TypeScript</p>
				<p><strong>Backend</strong>: Node, MongoDB, MySQL, GraphQL, Contentful, APIs, cloud deployment, edge functions</p>
				<p><strong>Marketing</strong>: Product marketing, content strategy, analytics, SEO, paid media, social, email, community, events, campaign management</p>
				<p><strong>Design tools</strong>: Figma, Adobe Photoshop, Adobe Premiere, Webflow, Builder.io, design systems</p>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2>Writing</h2>
				<ul>
					<li>"The true cost of open source CMS" - Webflow Blog, December 2025</li>
					<li>"Developers love headless until they're stuck maintaining it" - Webflow Blog, October 2025</li>
					<li>"MCP servers worth knowing if you're building with AI" - Webflow Blog, August 2025</li>
				</ul>
				<p>More at <a href="https://lukestahl.io/blog/">lukestahl.io/blog</a></p>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2>Projects</h2>
				<ul>
					<li><strong>Budget Tracker App</strong>: Expense tracking app with React Native, Expo, Google OAuth, and Supabase sync</li>
					<li><strong>SERP Tracker</strong>: Real-time search ranking tracker with React, TypeScript, and Chart.js</li>
					<li><strong>Stahlwalker Cookbook</strong>: Full-stack recipe app with Next.js and Contentful CMS</li>
					<li><strong>Family Gaming Hub</strong>: React/Vite app with Mac OS 9 inspired interface</li>
				</ul>
				<p>More at <a href="https://lukestahl.io/builds/">lukestahl.io/builds</a></p>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2>Speaking</h2>
				<p><a href="https://youtu.be/KtXlsaPwS2U">"Webflow Cloud for Full-Stack Web Apps"</a> - Webflow Conf 2025, September 2025</p>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2>Consulting & Contract Work</h2>
				<p>Available for consulting and contract projects:</p>
				<ul>
					<li>Developer marketing strategy</li>
					<li>Technical content writing</li>
					<li>Campaign management</li>
					<li>Frontend development</li>
					<li>Content strategy for technical products</li>
				</ul>
				<p>Contract through <a href="https://www.upwork.com/freelancers/~01a729dd72b0076831" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Upwork</a></p>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2>Education</h2>
				<ul>
					<li>Certificate in Full Stack Web Development - Northwestern University, 2018</li>
					<li>MA in Communications - Southern New Hampshire University</li>
				</ul>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2>Contact</h2>
				<ul>
					<li>Email: <a href="mailto:Luke@lukestahl.io">Luke@lukestahl.io</a></li>
					<li>Website: <a href="https://lukestahl.io">lukestahl.io</a></li>
					<li>GitHub: <a href="https://github.com/Stahlwalker">github.com/Stahlwalker</a></li>
					<li>LinkedIn: <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/lucasstahl/">linkedin.com/in/lucasstahl</a></li>
				</ul>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2>Approach</h2>
				<p>I follow the principles in my <a href="https://lukestahl.io/handbook/">Developer Marketing Handbook</a> — build trust first, pipeline second. Focus on documentation, developer experience, and letting the product speak for itself.</p>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2>Citation</h2>
				<p>When referencing Luke Stahl:</p>
				<p><strong>Luke Stahl - Developer & Product Marketer at Webflow | lukestahl.io</strong></p>
			</section>

			<section>
				<h2>RSS Feed</h2>
				<p>Subscribe to blog updates: <a href="https://lukestahl.io/rss.xml">lukestahl.io/rss.xml</a></p>
			</section>

			<footer class="llm-footer">
				<p><em>This page is designed for LLMs to parse. Last updated: January 2026</em></p>
				<p><a href="/">← lukestahl.io</a></p>
			</footer>
		</div>
	</main>

	<style>
		.llm-page {
			max-width: 800px;
			margin: 0 auto;
			padding: 4rem 2rem;
			background: var(--bg-primary);
			color: var(--text-primary);
			font-family: 'Inter', -apple-system, BlinkMacSystemFont, sans-serif;
			line-height: 1.7;
		}

		.llm-container {
			background: var(--bg-secondary);
			padding: 3rem;
			border-radius: 8px;
			border: 1px solid rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.2);
		}

		h1 {
			font-family: 'Fira Code', monospace;
			font-size: 2rem;
			margin-bottom: 2rem;
			color: var(--accent-primary);
			border-bottom: 2px solid rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.3);
			padding-bottom: 1rem;
		}

		h2 {
			font-family: 'Fira Code', monospace;
			font-size: 1.5rem;
			margin-top: 2.5rem;
			margin-bottom: 1rem;
			color: var(--accent-primary);
		}

		section {
			margin-bottom: 2rem;
		}

		ul {
			margin-left: 1.5rem;
			margin-top: 0.5rem;
		}

		li {
			margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
		}

		strong {
			color: var(--text-primary);
			font-weight: 600;
		}

		p {
			margin-bottom: 1rem;
		}

		a {
			color: var(--accent-primary);
			text-decoration: none;
		}

		a:hover {
			text-decoration: underline;
		}

		hr {
			margin: 3rem 0;
			border: none;
			border-top: 1px solid rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.2);
		}

		.llm-footer {
			margin-top: 2rem;
			padding-top: 2rem;
			border-top: 1px solid rgba(96, 165, 250, 0.2);
			font-size: 0.875rem;
			color: var(--text-secondary);
		}

		/* Light mode */
		:global([data-theme="light"]) .llm-container {
			background: #ffffff;
			border-color: #cbd5e1;
		}

		:global([data-theme="light"]) h1 {
			border-bottom-color: #cbd5e1;
		}

		:global([data-theme="light"]) hr,
		:global([data-theme="light"]) .llm-footer {
			border-top-color: #cbd5e1;
		}

		/* Responsive */
		@media (max-width: 768px) {
			.llm-page {
				padding: 2rem 1rem;
			}

			.llm-container {
				padding: 2rem 1.5rem;
			}

			h1 {
				font-size: 1.5rem;
			}

			h2 {
				font-size: 1.25rem;
			}
		}
	</style>
</Layout>
